---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Open cluster binary disruption";
import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Open cluster binary disruption</h1>

    <p>Binary disruption in open clusters is driven by close encounters, tidal stripping, and internal dynamical evolution. Key observables include the binary fraction as a function of time, separation (period), and mass ratio.</p>

    <h2>Recent work</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/zheng_2026_binary_disruption" text="Zheng et al. (2026)" /> — Two-stage disruption model; density scaling of disruption rates; public Python tool.</li>
    </ul>
  </main>
</Base>
